<sect1 id="POWER">
  <title>POWER</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">POWER<indexterm>
      <primary>POWER</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>POWER function</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis><emphasis>base,exponent</emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <para><informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="78.55pt" />

        <colspec colwidth="274.25pt" />

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><emphasis>base</emphasis></entry>

            <entry>The real number to raise.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><emphasis>exponent</emphasis></entry>

            <entry>The real power to raise x to.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry>Return:</entry>

            <entry>POWER returns a single real value.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">POWER </emphasis>function returns the result
  of the <emphasis>base </emphasis>raised to the <emphasis>exponent
  </emphasis>power.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <programlisting>MyCube := POWER(2.0,3.0); // = 8
MySquare := POWER(3.0,2.0); // = 9</programlisting>

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="SQRT">SQRT</link>, <link linkend="EXP">EXP</link>, <link linkend="LN">LN</link></para>
</sect1>
